      "writtenOn": "2026-04-20T11:44:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The current implementation also did not support a schema collection endpoint. It only registered individual schema file routes.\nMy dynamic implementation maintains the same behavior. I only handle individual schema file requests via /redfish/v1/schema/\u003cstr\u003e/, not a collection endpoint.\nThe allowlist check starts_with(\"/redfish/v1/schema/\") is intentional and correct:\n/redfish/v1/schema → does not match (no trailing slash, not allowed)\n/redfish/v1/schema/AccountService.xml → matches and proceeds to validation\nSo the schema collection endpoint is not on the allowlist and remains inaccessible, which is consistent with the existing behavior.",
      "parentUuid": "1307ae63_0e4690b8",
      "revId": "6ed5966df440b498570e290ba9f388dfc67d041d",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9d7994df_a5236186",
        "filename": "include/authentication.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 238,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000153
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-16T18:37:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Generally we don\u0027t allow starts_with type comparisons.  This is a security boundary, so we need to be somewhat specific, that\u0027s why the old check used a specific list of routes.  If someone registered /redfish/v1/schema/sensitive_data, this would allow them through.\n\nlet me think on this a bit on how to solve this, as your use case makes sense, but this check was very intentionally not a starts_with type request.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 234,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 238,
        "endChar": 9
      },
      "revId": "6ed5966df440b498570e290ba9f388dfc67d041d",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d5f7e292_9908131b",
        "filename": "include/authentication.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 238,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002926
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-20T11:44:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thank you for the feedback. I understand the security concern with using starts_with here. My intent was to allow only schema XML files to be accessed without authentication, but I agree that a more precise check is safer. I\u0027ve updated the check to be more specific. \nThis approach:\nOnly allows URLs matching the pattern - /redfish/v1/schema/\u003cfilename\u003e.xml\nEnsures the filename is not empty - (prevents /redfish/v1/schema/.xml)\nDisallows subdirectories - (prevents /redfish/v1/schema/subdir/file.xml)\nThis maintains the security boundary while allowing the legitimate use case of serving XML schema files dynamically. Please let me know if you\u0027d like any further refinements.",
      "parentUuid": "9d7994df_a5236186",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 234,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 238,
        "endChar": 9
      },
